*blogtk-2.0-r1 (17 Jan 2013)

  17 Jan 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> +blogtk-2.0-r1.ebuild:
  Bump to eapi5, use python-single-r1.eclass and fix desktop file (#451588 by
  G.Wolfe Woodbury)

  08 Jun 2012; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> metadata.xml:
  Drop maintainer from metadata as talked with him, bug #90641.

  05 May 2012; Jeff Horelick <jdhore@gentoo.org> blogtk-2.0.ebuild:
  dev-util/pkgconfig -> virtual/pkgconfig

  05 Feb 2012; Mike Gilbert <floppym@gentoo.org> blogtk-2.0.ebuild:
  Inherit multilib.

  24 Oct 2011; Alexandre Rostovtsev <tetromino@gentoo.org> blogtk-2.0.ebuild:
  Depend on correct slot of pygobject.

  14 Jan 2011; Gilles Dartiguelongue <eva@gentoo.org> -blogtk-1.0.ebuild,
  -files/blogtk-1.0-destdir.patch, -blogtk-1.1.ebuild,
  -files/blogtk-1.1-destdir.patch, -files/blogtk-1.1-makefile.patch:
  Clean up old revisions.

  13 Jan 2011; Brent Baude <ranger@gentoo.org> blogtk-2.0.ebuild:
  stable ppc, bug 345137

  14 Nov 2010; Markus Meier <maekke@gentoo.org> blogtk-2.0.ebuild:
  x86 stable, bug #345137

  12 Nov 2010; Markos Chandras <hwoarang@gentoo.org> blogtk-2.0.ebuild:
  Stable on amd64 wrt bug #345137

  06 Oct 2010; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> blogtk-2.0.ebuild:
  Fix install on non-lib64 systems (bug #339696 reported by Diego E.
  'Flameeyes' Pettenò and fix by Gilles Dartiguelongue), also add missing
  RDEPENDs.

*blogtk-2.0 (18 Sep 2010)

